00:19:01.260 --> 00:19:03.260
Matt Ridley: Mark, eno vprašanje.

00:19:03.260 --> 00:19:06.260
Svante je ugotovil, da so gen FOXP2,

00:19:06.260 --> 00:19:08.260
ki naj bi bil povezan z jezikom,

00:19:08.260 --> 00:19:10.260
v isti obliki kot mi imeli tudi

00:19:10.260 --> 00:19:12.260
neandertalci.

00:19:12.260 --> 00:19:14.260
Ali morda vemo,

00:19:14.260 --> 00:19:16.260
kako bi bili lahko premagali neandertalce,

00:19:16.260 --> 00:19:18.260
če bi tudi oni imeli jezik?

00:19:18.260 --> 00:19:20.260
Mark Pagel: To je dobro vprašanje.

00:19:20.260 --> 00:19:23.260
Mnogi med vami poznate idejo o genu FOXP2,

00:19:23.260 --> 00:19:26.260
ki naj bi bil na nek način povezan

00:19:26.260 --> 00:19:29.260
z nadzorom fine motorike, potrebne za jezik.

00:19:29.260 --> 00:19:31.260
Ne verjamem, da nam to pove,

00:19:31.260 --> 00:19:33.260
da so neandertalci imeli jezik,

00:19:33.260 --> 00:19:36.260
in sicer zaradi enostavne analogije:

00:19:36.260 --> 00:19:39.260
Ferrari je avto, ki ima motor.

00:19:39.260 --> 00:19:41.260
Moj avto ima motor,

00:19:41.260 --> 00:19:43.260
ampak ni Ferrari.

00:19:43.260 --> 00:19:45.260
Enostaven odgovor na to je,

00:19:45.260 --> 00:19:47.260
da geni sami po sebi

00:19:47.260 --> 00:19:49.260
ne določajo rezultata

00:19:49.260 --> 00:19:51.260
tako zapletene stvari, kot je jezik.

00:19:51.260 --> 00:19:53.260
Kar vemo o FOXP2 in neandertalcih, je,

00:19:53.260 --> 00:19:57.260
da so morda imeli fino motoriko ust -- kdo ve.

00:19:57.260 --> 00:19:59.260
A to nam ne pove nujno, da so imeli jezik.

